and the sniff.

30:03.200 --> 30:05.400
He says it's hay fever,
but it'll be a brain tumor

30:05.440 --> 30:07.000
resting on his sinus
or something.

30:07.040 --> 30:08.560
I hate his friends.

30:08.600 --> 30:10.000
Not all his friends,
but a lot of his friends.

30:10.040 --> 30:13.000
I mean, they don't get me.
I don't get them.

30:13.040 --> 30:17.520
I mean, what is
transfer pricing?

30:17.560 --> 30:20.440
[Chuckles] Right.

30:23.200 --> 30:26.920
There's this, um, film

30:26.960 --> 30:29.240
I'm making for
the wedding -- all this film.

30:29.280 --> 30:32.200
And, um, I'm not in half of it,
but they are --

30:32.240 --> 30:36.400
Hannah and Nina --
with my dad.

30:36.440 --> 30:38.040
He was gone for a long time,
but now he's back.

30:38.080 --> 30:41.400
And it hurts
because, um...

30:41.440 --> 30:43.560
[Smacks lips]

30:43.600 --> 30:47.400
...I always had my sisters
and my mother,

30:47.440 --> 30:49.200
and they were enough.

30:49.240 --> 30:51.360
And then I found
these tapes,

30:51.400 --> 30:55.160
and I started to see it --
this hole.

30:55.200 --> 30:58.920
And it feels w-weird
because...

31:03.840 --> 31:08.320
...because,
uh, I miss him.

31:13.320 --> 31:15.040
[Chuckles]

31:20.080 --> 31:24.680
I miss my dad, even though --
even though he's here.

31:31.640 --> 31:34.600
Oh...my God.

31:37.200 --> 31:38.480
[Laughs]

31:38.520 --> 31:40.800
-Oh! Oh!
-Are you a believer now?

31:40.840 --> 31:42.560
Thank you! Thank you![Chuckles]

31:42.600 --> 31:45.080
Oh, gosh.

31:49.000 --> 31:50.120
[Gasps]

31:50.160 --> 31:52.240
[Light clattering]

31:52.280 --> 31:53.800
[Breathes sharply]

31:53.840 --> 31:55.200
Uh, uh...

31:55.240 --> 31:57.240
I'm -- I'm...

31:57.280 --> 31:58.960
♪♪

31:59.000 --> 32:01.920
Oh, my God.

32:01.960 --> 32:03.080
I'm so sorry.

32:03.120 --> 32:06.080
-Uh...
-Oh, my God.

32:06.120 --> 32:07.920
Uh, R-Ro--

32:07.960 --> 32:09.360
Oh!

32:09.400 --> 32:10.600
Rose?

32:10.640 --> 32:11.760
Rose?

32:11.800 --> 32:12.840
[Door creaks]

32:12.880 --> 32:15.080
[Door closes]

32:15.120 --> 32:23.520
♪♪

32:23.560 --> 32:26.840
Keep calm. Answer all
the questions succinctly.

32:26.880 --> 32:30.640
Don't let yourself get riled.
Trust in the system.

32:30.680 --> 32:32.360
No Christie?

32:32.400 --> 32:34.560
Must be running late.

32:34.600 --> 32:36.400
[Indistinct conversations]

32:36.440 --> 32:37.960
[Gasps]

32:38.000 --> 32:40.160
Elliot!

32:40.200 --> 32:42.800
Look at me!
Look at me!

32:42.840 --> 32:44.760
We went to Whitstable,
and we sat on the beach,

32:44.800 --> 32:46.160
and we made plans.

32:46.200 --> 32:47.640
-We agreed.
-Let's go in and sit down.

32:47.680 --> 32:49.920
You promised!

32:49.960 --> 32:51.440
Elliot!

32:51.480 --> 32:53.720
You promised me
those embryos!

32:53.760 --> 32:55.320
[Door opens]

32:55.360 --> 32:56.720
Mr. Lee,
would you say your wife

32:56.760 --> 33:00.000
has been fair to you
over the years?Yes.

33:00.040 --> 33:01.880
She settled
both the mortgages

33:01.920 --> 33:04.360
on your mother
and brother's houses.

33:04.400 --> 33:06.200
She's also, over the course
of the last five years,

33:06.240 --> 33:09.440
transferred properties
in Switzerland and Long Island

33:09.480 --> 33:11.360
into your name.Yes.

33:11.400 --> 33:14.360
So, you would say
she's a very generous woman?

33:14.400 --> 33:16.360
She has been.
In the past.

33:16.400 --> 33:20.200
£30,000 a year for
a personal trainer, Mr. Lee?

33:20.240 --> 33:23.560
£100,000 for travel?

33:23.600 --> 33:27.760
This brings me
to a question of conduct.

33:27.800 --> 33:30.720
I'd like to refer
to an e-mail

33:30.760 --> 33:33.560
received by Mrs. Lee
from you

33:33.600 --> 33:36.880
early yesterday morning.

33:36.920 --> 33:40.760
We strongly disagree
with this line of questioning.

33:40.800 --> 33:45.840
This is a personal e-mail
sent at a highly emotional time.

33:45.880 --> 33:48.640
Judge Lyle:
I'm going to allow it.

33:48.680 --> 33:52.480
Uh, if you would look at
the e-mail, please, Mr. Lee...

33:52.520 --> 33:55.080
In it, you agree to settle
on all our points

33:55.120 --> 33:57.560
for a one-off payment
of £30 million,

33:57.600 --> 33:59.560
and for that,
your wife keeps

33:59.600 --> 34:05.120
all other "assets"
from the marriage.

34:05.160 --> 34:07.360
Elliot:
I was drunk.

34:07.400 --> 34:10.160
And yet you still
make promises.

34:10.200 --> 34:14.160
Promises that we can't
be sure you will keep,

34:14.200 --> 34:15.600
like promising my client,

34:15.640 --> 34:18.280
while she was undergoing
her cancer treatment,

34:18.320 --> 34:20.080
that she would one day
have children.

34:20.120 --> 34:22.040
Why do you do this,
Mr. Lee?

34:22.080 --> 34:24.000
'Cause I...

34:24.040 --> 34:26.240
Answer the question.

34:26.280 --> 34:30.560
♪♪

34:30.600 --> 34:33.440
Answer the question.

34:33.480 --> 34:35.480
Because I didn't
think she'd live.

34:35.520 --> 34:40.680
♪♪

34:40.720 --> 34:43.080
I'm so sorry.
Excuse me.

34:43.120 --> 34:44.640
[Footsteps]

34:44.680 --> 34:48.320
♪♪

34:48.360 --> 34:49.720
[Door opens]

34:52.160 --> 34:56.320
[Breathing deeply]

34:56.360 --> 35:03.680
♪♪

35:03.720 --> 35:05.760
[Sniffles]

35:05.800 --> 35:11.880
♪♪

35:11.920 --> 35:17.360
They tell you to imagine
a control room in chemo to --

35:17.400 --> 35:19.600
to walk into it,

35:19.640 --> 35:23.600
to stand,
and to look at your life,

35:23.640 --> 35:28.520
to look at all your failings
and all the things you regret.

35:28.560 --> 35:32.280
And then they tell you
to take all of that darkness,

35:32.320 --> 35:36.640
take the driving seat,
and move towards the light.

35:36.680 --> 35:39.520
♪♪

35:39.560 --> 35:42.160
In that light
were those children.

35:42.200 --> 35:45.440
♪♪

35:45.480 --> 35:46.800
Jaynie.

35:46.840 --> 35:49.800
I've always wanted
a family.

35:49.840 --> 35:52.880
Everything in this world
is for four --

35:52.920 --> 35:56.000
family meals,
family discounts.

35:56.040 --> 35:57.720
"Is it just
a table for one?

35:57.760 --> 36:00.200
Because we've got a booth
if you've got your kids."

36:00.240 --> 36:03.960
♪♪

36:04.000 --> 36:06.280
Give him what he wants.

36:06.320 --> 36:08.240
But he could still
withdraw consent.

36:08.280 --> 36:12.680
You've only got one life.
And I won't live with regret.

36:12.720 --> 36:20.280
♪♪

36:20.320 --> 36:28.080
♪♪

36:28.120 --> 36:30.640
I would like to
strongly remind everyone

36:30.680 --> 36:34.960
that I am approving
a financial order only.

36:35.000 --> 36:37.840
Three payments of
£10 million each

36:37.880 --> 36:41.840
to be scattered
over a 12-month period.

36:41.880 --> 36:44.440
Additional assets as agreed.

36:44.480 --> 36:46.880
♪♪

36:46.920 --> 36:48.480
Mrs. Lee...

36:48.520 --> 36:51.960
I hope today will bring you
some kind of peace.

36:52.000 --> 36:54.480
Bailiff: All rise.

36:54.520 --> 37:03.800
♪♪

37:03.840 --> 37:11.720
♪♪

37:11.760 --> 37:13.520
[Footsteps]

37:13.560 --> 37:15.560
♪♪

37:15.600 --> 37:17.000
[Door opens]

37:17.040 --> 37:22.400
♪♪

37:22.440 --> 37:26.240
Zander: So, overall,
a very healthy quarter.

37:26.280 --> 37:28.960
Okay, go, go, go. I need you
to keep earning the money.

37:29.000 --> 37:34.360
♪♪

37:34.400 --> 37:36.600
[Door opens]

37:36.640 --> 37:39.440
Hannah.
Yeah?

37:39.480 --> 37:42.120
Jaynie Lee,
how did it go?[Door closes]

37:42.160 --> 37:43.800
Uh, she settled.

37:43.840 --> 37:46.400
Let's hope her husband keeps
his promise about the embryos.

37:46.440 --> 37:48.160
Nathan did what
he could, but --

37:48.200 --> 37:50.760
Did that work out okay?
With Nathan?

37:50.800 --> 37:52.600
Yep. Good.

37:52.640 --> 37:54.760
Uh, he's a good
barrister.

37:54.800 --> 37:56.360
He is.

37:56.400 --> 37:58.480
And was everything okay
with you and Christie?

38:00.680 --> 38:01.960
Yes.

38:02.000 --> 38:04.240
Things seem
a little...

38:04.280 --> 38:07.160
heated between
the two of you

38:07.200 --> 38:09.600
at the party
the other night.

38:11.480 --> 38:14.200
[Sighs]

38:14.240 --> 38:18.960
Whatever the problem is,
I need him back on his game.

38:19.000 --> 38:23.480
Out there...fine.

38:23.520 --> 38:26.480
But in here,
you work for Noble & Hale.

38:31.920 --> 38:33.400
We good?

38:33.440 --> 38:35.200
Mm-hmm. Yep.
[Chuckles]

38:38.000 --> 38:40.840
Oh. Your mother.

38:40.880 --> 38:44.520
[Whistles]
What a dame!

38:45.400 --> 38:46.560
[Indistinct conversations]

38:46.600 --> 38:47.800
♪♪

38:47.840 --> 38:49.480
Davey McKenzie's files.

38:49.520 --> 38:51.480
They've just arrived
from Defoe's.

38:51.520 --> 38:53.000
They sent a truck full.

38:53.040 --> 38:54.320
Ohh.

38:54.360 --> 38:56.640
♪♪

38:56.680 --> 39:00.600
Any unusual expenditure
please mark up on the board.

39:00.640 --> 39:02.760
♪♪

39:02.800 --> 39:04.840
Order pizza.

39:04.880 --> 39:06.960
We may be here some time.

39:07.000 --> 39:08.440
♪♪

39:08.480 --> 39:10.200
Takeaway?

39:10.240 --> 39:12.360
Uh, fine, fine.[Doorbell rings]

39:12.400 --> 39:14.160
[Bottle thumps lightly]

39:14.200 --> 39:16.200
[Indistinct conversations
on television]

39:16.960 --> 39:18.200
[Door creaks lightly]

39:18.240 --> 39:20.320
I bring weapons.

39:21.720 --> 39:23.360
You must be Nathan.

39:24.920 --> 39:27.000
I'm Oscar,
Hannah's father.

39:28.480 --> 39:33.080
Uh, uh, Hannah's
still at work.

39:33.120 --> 39:34.600
Does she know
you're here?

39:34.640 --> 39:36.560
No, I'm --
I'm so sorry.

39:36.600 --> 39:38.360
Is it terribly
inconvenient?

39:38.400 --> 39:39.840
I can come back.

39:42.760 --> 39:45.640
You must be Matilda.

39:45.680 --> 39:48.280
No, he's Vinnie.
I'm Tilly.

39:48.320 --> 39:49.800
Oscar: Oh.Liv.

39:49.840 --> 39:51.280
My mother's name!

39:51.320 --> 39:52.560
But you're much prettier.

39:52.600 --> 39:54.320
Now, where
do I put these bags?

39:57.200 --> 39:58.440
Lead on.

39:58.480 --> 40:00.800
[Footsteps]

40:02.520 --> 40:04.360
Pizza's arrived.

40:07.560 --> 40:08.680
[Indistinct conversations]

40:08.720 --> 40:10.440
You want me
to bring you some?

40:10.480 --> 40:11.680
No, I'm fine.

40:11.720 --> 40:13.680
Sorry.

40:13.720 --> 40:15.080
Found anything?

40:15.120 --> 40:17.080
One or two
interesting deposits.

40:17.120 --> 40:19.040
Uh-huh.[Papers rustle]

40:19.080 --> 40:22.040
[Cellphone rings]

40:22.080 --> 40:24.720
They go back a long way.

40:24.760 --> 40:26.600
[Ringing stops]

40:26.640 --> 40:30.040
[Indistinct conversations]

40:30.080 --> 40:31.120
Hm?

40:33.640 --> 40:35.360
It's nothing.
[Laughs]

40:35.400 --> 40:38.200
We're just friends.Yeah, with benefits.

40:40.440 --> 40:43.160
Didn't you ever
have one of those?

40:44.480 --> 40:45.640
[Footsteps]

40:48.920 --> 40:51.200
Blah!
Have you heard that one?

40:51.240 --> 40:53.560
Ugh. It's disgusting. [Cellphone ringing]

40:53.600 --> 40:56.320
Nina: [Sighs] Nathan.Mayday.
This is not a rehearsal.

40:56.360 --> 40:57.920
We're at DEFCON 1.

40:57.960 --> 40:59.680
Your father is here,
shamelessly corrupting the kids

40:59.720 --> 41:02.560
with Nerf guns
and Beanboozled.

41:02.600 --> 41:04.480
What are Beanboozled?

41:04.520 --> 41:05.840
Taste like dog food.

41:05.880 --> 41:07.160
Hannah's not
answering.

41:07.200 --> 41:10.080
Oh, God. Okay.

41:10.120 --> 41:11.960
[Receiver clicks]

41:12.000 --> 41:13.560
Mmm!

41:13.600 --> 41:15.080
This one tastes
like strawberries, I think.

41:15.120 --> 41:16.480
[Children laugh]

41:16.520 --> 41:19.480
Nina's on her way.Oh, good!
You got Spotify?!

41:19.520 --> 41:22.000
Mm-hmm.Yeah! Let's get it on!

41:22.040 --> 41:23.600
Vinnie.
Oh!

41:23.640 --> 41:24.800
Let me do it.

41:24.840 --> 41:26.480
That cover
matches my scarf.

41:26.520 --> 41:28.560
Vinnie!
Aah!

41:28.600 --> 41:30.280
Aah, aah, aah!
[Laughs]

41:30.320 --> 41:31.520
[Indistinct shouting]Liv!

41:33.560 --> 41:38.320
♪♪

41:38.360 --> 41:40.600
[Sighs]

41:40.640 --> 41:47.600
♪♪

41:47.640 --> 41:50.400
♪♪

41:50.440 --> 41:52.040
[Pen taps lightly]

41:52.080 --> 41:53.200
[Dialing]

41:53.240 --> 41:54.440
[Sniffles]

41:54.480 --> 42:01.560
♪♪

42:01.600 --> 42:06.400
[Cellphone rings]

42:06.440 --> 42:07.880
Hello?

42:07.920 --> 42:10.560
Hannah: Goldie,
I'm sorry to call late.

42:10.600 --> 42:12.280
But I'm looking
at the accounts,

42:12.320 --> 42:13.880
uh, Davey sent over.

42:13.920 --> 42:16.560
Now, there are transfers
to this account

42:16.600 --> 42:18.600
that go back
about 10 years.

42:18.640 --> 42:21.360
We're talking on average
a million pounds a year.

42:21.400 --> 42:24.960
But it's --
it's a serial number,

42:25.000 --> 42:27.240
rather than
a named account.

42:27.280 --> 42:29.560
Do you have any idea
who that could belong to?

42:29.600 --> 42:35.720
♪♪

42:35.760 --> 42:38.360
C-Could I call you back?

42:38.400 --> 42:41.600
It's just there's
someone I need to...

42:41.640 --> 42:44.520
Sure.

42:44.560 --> 42:45.960
[Cellphone thumps lightly]

42:46.000 --> 42:49.760
♪♪

42:49.800 --> 42:52.760
[Crying]

42:52.800 --> 42:55.080
[Sobs]

42:55.120 --> 42:58.280
♪♪

42:58.320 --> 42:59.880
[Sobs]

42:59.920 --> 43:01.960
♪♪

43:02.000 --> 43:03.240
[Beeps]

43:03.280 --> 43:05.800
♪♪

43:05.840 --> 43:07.240
Hmm.

43:07.280 --> 43:08.440
[Cellphone thumps lightly]

43:08.480 --> 43:10.120
♪ To get to the big time

43:10.160 --> 43:12.280
Go big or go home.I love you.

43:12.320 --> 43:16.040
♪ I'll make a big noise Oh, the memory of
showtunes.

43:16.080 --> 43:18.560
♪ Do wonderful things It's all coming back.

43:18.600 --> 43:20.440
Get glasses.
It's the only way through.

43:20.480 --> 43:22.920
♪ I've got a bluebird

43:22.960 --> 43:25.000
[Door creaks lightly]

43:30.560 --> 43:32.320
[Door closes]

43:44.200 --> 43:45.960
[Cellphone chimes]

43:49.960 --> 43:51.800
[Footsteps approaching]

43:51.840 --> 43:53.600
In my defense,

43:53.640 --> 43:56.760
I was exceptionally drunk
when I called on Nina.

43:56.800 --> 43:58.160
Oh, uh -- Oh, God,
I'm -- I'm over it.

43:58.200 --> 44:01.560
I've -- I've -- I've got
a ton of work,

44:01.600 --> 44:03.400
and, um, right now,

44:03.440 --> 44:07.640
my father is at my house
doing God knows what.

44:07.680 --> 44:09.520
So can we just talk about
this another time, please?

44:09.560 --> 44:10.840
You made a choice.
[Sighs]

44:10.880 --> 44:12.360
Really, Christie?
You want to do this now?

44:12.400 --> 44:13.920
I get it.
Oh.[Cellphone chimes]

44:13.960 --> 44:16.720
I-I get Nathan and you,
and I-I-I'm glad you're happy.

44:16.760 --> 44:18.360
I-I-I-I want you
to be happy.

44:18.400 --> 44:20.400
It's just that --Oh, I have --
I have to go.

44:21.840 --> 44:23.640
[Footsteps]

44:23.680 --> 44:25.880
[Door opens]

44:28.280 --> 44:29.960
[Sighs]

44:30.640 --> 44:31.840
[ Elevator bell chimes ]

44:31.880 --> 44:34.680
[Sighs][Door closes]

44:34.720 --> 44:36.440
Wow.

44:36.480 --> 44:39.040
♪ Or meet me by the car

44:39.080 --> 44:42.480
♪ 'Cause it's not parked
very far ♪

44:42.520 --> 44:44.680
♪ We're spending time

44:44.720 --> 44:46.520
♪ And we're wasting
our youth ♪

44:46.560 --> 44:49.160
♪ We're stuck in
a kissing booth ♪

44:49.200 --> 44:52.640
♪ So tell me two steps
and I'll follow ♪

44:52.680 --> 44:56.760
♪ I'll give you two steps,
and you'll follow ♪

44:56.800 --> 45:00.480
[Indistinct conversations]

45:00.520 --> 45:04.840
Oscar: We're going on a Kamikaze
mission, ready? Yah!

45:04.880 --> 45:09.000
-You haven't got a flag.
-Ah!

45:09.040 --> 45:10.920
[Laughter]He caught me on the front.

45:10.960 --> 45:12.720
Ow! What the --

45:12.760 --> 45:15.120
Nina:
Hannah! H-Hannah!

45:15.160 --> 45:16.960
Nathan and I called
several times.

45:17.000 --> 45:20.440
This is what happens when
you don't answer your phone.

45:20.480 --> 45:23.040
Resistance was futile!

45:23.080 --> 45:24.400
Vinnie:
He's going to run, Mum!

45:24.440 --> 45:26.120
Seriously?
Seriously!

45:26.160 --> 45:28.360
-I'm not doing this.
-I'm reloading!

45:28.400 --> 45:30.040
This is not
my idea of fun!

45:30.080 --> 45:31.040
-Ow!
-Take down the young first!

45:31.080 --> 45:34.360
-Over here.
-Right.

45:34.400 --> 45:35.520
Ow!

45:35.560 --> 45:38.120
[Indistinct shouting]

45:38.160 --> 45:44.920
♪♪

45:44.960 --> 45:46.680
[Shouting continues]

45:46.720 --> 45:48.800
♪♪

45:48.840 --> 45:50.280
Cover me, cover me!

45:50.320 --> 45:53.720
[Shouting continues]

45:53.760 --> 45:55.800
Ow!

45:55.840 --> 45:57.840
Yay!

45:57.880 --> 46:01.840
[Indistinct shouting
and laughter]

46:01.880 --> 46:03.920
♪♪

46:12.600 --> 46:14.880
[Dog barking in distance]

46:19.560 --> 46:22.320
[Doorbell rings]

46:22.360 --> 46:25.120
Boy: Mum,
someone's at the door!

46:29.080 --> 46:32.160
For your son.

46:32.200 --> 46:33.880
He is yours,
isn't he?

46:37.800 --> 46:39.720
Yeah.

46:39.760 --> 46:41.720
[Scoffs]

46:45.320 --> 46:47.400
I-I'm sorry.
I'm sorry! I'm sor--

46:47.440 --> 46:50.680
Goldie, please.

46:50.720 --> 46:52.760
You always
wanted three.

46:55.800 --> 46:57.520
[Footsteps]

46:59.800 --> 47:04.080
Oscar: Oh, oh.
"Cake free and dried.

47:04.120 --> 47:07.240
Hum...Yum..."

47:10.040 --> 47:12.760
You don't read to him
anymore, do you?

47:12.800 --> 47:15.760
No, not since
he was 8.

47:15.800 --> 47:18.120
He was humoring me.

47:20.560 --> 47:23.360
What time is it?
Late.

47:23.400 --> 47:24.560
Home.

47:28.200 --> 47:29.760
I'll drive you.

47:31.360 --> 47:34.080
Thank you.

47:38.840 --> 47:40.200
[Light switch clicks]

47:40.240 --> 47:42.200
Nathan: It's controversial,
but he's okay.

47:42.240 --> 47:44.960
[Sighs]
You've drunk too much.

47:45.000 --> 47:47.080
You're horrible.
You're...
[Scoffs]

47:47.120 --> 47:49.440
Oh, you're both
horrible.

47:49.480 --> 47:51.120
[Sighs]

47:54.240 --> 47:56.680
I -- I don't really
know any of you.

47:56.720 --> 47:58.240
None of you ever
really let me in.[Sighs]

47:58.280 --> 48:00.080
You know what it's like
always feeling

48:00.120 --> 48:01.600
the outsider
with you lot?

48:03.280 --> 48:04.840
I mean...

48:04.880 --> 48:07.160
It's like watching
people live with ghosts.

48:07.200 --> 48:09.240
It's a relief to
finally meet him.

48:09.280 --> 48:10.720
Wh--
What?

48:10.760 --> 48:13.160
It's not easy.
None of you are easy.

48:13.200 --> 48:16.360
Rose is easy.
Rose is nice.

48:16.400 --> 48:17.880
You don't like men.

48:17.920 --> 48:19.240
Well -- Pbht.
None of you.

48:19.280 --> 48:20.640
Well, you don't,
none of you.

48:20.680 --> 48:24.000
You tolerate them,
but you don't like them.

48:24.040 --> 48:26.640
Hannah barely
tolerates me.

48:26.680 --> 48:28.560
Well, that's not true.

48:28.600 --> 48:31.000
We never have sex --

48:31.040 --> 48:33.120
doesn't want it, ever.

48:36.680 --> 48:38.000
[Clattering lightly]

48:38.040 --> 48:41.800
[Sighs, scoffs]

48:41.840 --> 48:42.840
I like you, Nina.

48:42.880 --> 48:44.280
[Breathes deeply]

48:44.320 --> 48:45.560
I like you, Nathan.

48:45.600 --> 48:48.800
[Laughs]

48:48.840 --> 48:51.160
[Sighs]

48:51.200 --> 48:54.040
Okay. Uh, Nathan.

48:54.080 --> 48:56.200
No, don't be weird!

48:59.360 --> 49:02.200
Hannah: Nina?

49:02.240 --> 49:06.440
I'm driving him back!
Want a lift?

49:06.480 --> 49:08.600
Fine.
You can drop me at Mum's.

49:08.640 --> 49:09.760
I'll --
Yeah.

49:09.800 --> 49:11.640
I'll stay at Mum's
tonight.

49:15.480 --> 49:17.800
Idiot.

49:17.840 --> 49:20.240
[Sighs]

49:20.280 --> 49:22.400
♪♪

49:22.440 --> 49:23.960
Shit.

49:24.000 --> 49:31.520
♪♪

49:31.560 --> 49:32.920
Ugh.

49:34.760 --> 49:36.240
[Car door shuts]

49:36.280 --> 49:38.080
[Seat belt clicks]

49:38.120 --> 49:40.600
Hannah:
[Sighs] Okay?

49:40.640 --> 49:44.200
Oscar: Yeah, I just can't do
late nights anymore.

49:44.240 --> 49:46.280
[Engine starts]

49:46.320 --> 49:54.000
♪♪

49:54.040 --> 50:01.760
♪♪

50:01.800 --> 50:09.480
♪♪

50:09.520 --> 50:17.200
♪♪

50:17.240 --> 50:20.120
Shh, go back to sleep.

50:20.160 --> 50:29.800
♪♪

50:29.840 --> 50:33.120
[Crying]

50:39.120 --> 50:45.080
[Keys jingle]

50:45.120 --> 50:49.480
[Door opens]

50:49.520 --> 50:50.800
[Light switch clicks]

50:50.840 --> 50:52.320
[Keys thump]

50:56.200 --> 50:58.000
Hannah:
Can I come in?

51:17.080 --> 51:21.320
[Water running]

51:32.520 --> 51:34.960
I didn't know we still
had this place.

51:35.000 --> 51:37.320
I need to sit down.

51:41.040 --> 51:42.840
[Light switch clicks]

51:44.080 --> 51:45.680
[Sighs]

51:45.720 --> 51:47.240
[Groans lightly]

51:53.400 --> 51:55.680
There's still a burn
in the carpet.

51:58.080 --> 51:59.640
Huh.

51:59.680 --> 52:03.720
'Cause Nina tried to make
a bonfire for her Sindy.

52:03.760 --> 52:05.280
[Chuckles]

52:05.320 --> 52:07.880
Grandpa threatened to throw her
out of the kitchen window.

52:10.080 --> 52:12.600
I had to talk him down.

52:18.000 --> 52:20.560
So, uh, you need
our three signatures.

52:20.600 --> 52:23.640
Uh, if -- if it's just
about the money,

52:23.680 --> 52:25.520
we'll buy you out.
Hannah.

52:25.560 --> 52:27.080
You don't need
to do all this.

52:27.120 --> 52:28.760
I d-- I don't want you
to do all this.

52:28.800 --> 52:30.920
It's -- It's not --I don't want my kids
to like you.

52:32.640 --> 52:34.480
[Sniffles]

52:45.880 --> 52:49.520
Nothing...

52:49.560 --> 52:51.240
for 30 years.

52:59.520 --> 53:01.360
We wrote.

53:03.560 --> 53:06.720
W-We sent presents
every birthday.

53:06.760 --> 53:08.320
For -- For years.

53:08.360 --> 53:10.640
Uh, Easter, Christmas.

53:10.680 --> 53:12.480
A -- A telegram
for -- for --

53:12.520 --> 53:14.440
for when you
married Nathan.

53:19.440 --> 53:22.080
Did you get anything?

53:25.280 --> 53:26.560
[Crying]

53:26.600 --> 53:28.920
No. No.

53:28.960 --> 53:30.840
Han-- Hannah.[Door opens]

53:30.880 --> 53:33.240
Ohh.[Door slams shut]

53:37.040 --> 53:39.160
[Engine revs]

53:42.040 --> 53:43.440
[Keys jingle]

53:44.320 --> 53:45.320
[Door slams]

53:48.640 --> 53:50.400
Ruth: What?

53:51.760 --> 53:54.640
Hannah?

53:56.920 --> 53:58.600
Hannah?

53:58.640 --> 54:00.240
Hannah!
Nothing!

54:00.280 --> 54:02.520
Stop it!
You say nothing!

54:02.560 --> 54:03.920
What?

54:03.960 --> 54:06.680
What?

54:06.720 --> 54:09.400
Hannah, what do you
think you're doing?

54:10.840 --> 54:12.280
[Creaks]

54:12.320 --> 54:13.720
Is this what a nervous
breakdown looks like?

54:13.760 --> 54:15.720
[Both laugh]

54:15.760 --> 54:18.800
Liar. Liar.

54:18.840 --> 54:20.000
Liar!

54:20.040 --> 54:22.040
[Closet door creaks]

54:24.040 --> 54:25.200
[Clattering]

54:27.080 --> 54:28.280
[Sighs]

54:34.280 --> 54:36.720
The key --
I want -- I want the key.

54:36.760 --> 54:38.280
Give -- Give me
the key, Mother,

54:38.320 --> 54:40.800
or I will break it
over your head.

54:44.080 --> 54:45.200
[Box scraping]

54:45.240 --> 54:46.640
[Breathes heavily]

54:46.680 --> 54:47.720
[Box scraping]

54:47.760 --> 54:49.360
[Breathes sharply]

54:52.120 --> 54:54.120
[Box unlocking]

54:58.160 --> 55:00.560
♪♪

55:00.600 --> 55:03.440
[Crying]

55:03.480 --> 55:05.400
No. [Sobs]

55:05.440 --> 55:09.560
♪♪

55:09.600 --> 55:12.080
-Hannah --
-[Crying] No!

55:12.120 --> 55:20.880
♪♪

55:20.920 --> 55:29.720
♪♪

55:29.760 --> 55:38.520
♪♪

55:38.560 --> 55:47.320
♪♪

55:47.360 --> 55:56.120
♪♪

55:56.160 --> 56:04.960
♪♪

56:05.000 --> 56:13.760
♪♪

56:13.800 --> 56:15.160
He left you.

56:15.200 --> 56:18.600
♪♪

56:18.640 --> 56:20.480
He didn't leave us.

56:20.520 --> 56:24.320
♪♪

